member.param:
A lambda expression representing the property to be used as the primary key. 
            C#: t => t.Id VB.Net: Function(t) t.Id If the primary key is made up of multiple properties then specify an anonymous type
            including the properties. C#: t => new { t.Id1, t.Id2 } VB.Net: Function(t) New With { t.Id1, t.Id2 }

A lambda expression representing the property to be indexed. 
            C#: t => t.PropertyOne VB.Net: Function(t) t.PropertyOne If multiple properties are to be indexed 
            then specify an anonymous type including the properties. C#: t => new { t.PropertyOne, t.PropertyTwo } 
            VB.Net: Function(t) New With { t.PropertyOne, t.PropertyTwo }
